[1] Cholera - Zambia (Namwala)
Date: Tue, 11 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Post (Lusaka) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200604110278.html>

Cholera has broken out in Ndeema area of Namwala district where 3
people have been admitted to 2 treatment centers. Namwala district
commissioner Eunice Nawa confirmed the outbreak yesterday, 10 Apr
2006, but said there had been no deaths so far.
Nawa said 2 cholera patients were admitted to Ichila health center
while 1 was receiving treatment at Chitongo health center. She said
all the 3 patients were in stable condition. Nawa said the Ministry
of Health in Namwala had established the source of the disease as
Bweengwa. She said 5 people from Ndeema area in chief Muchila
travelled to Bweengwa for a funeral where they are suspected to have
contracted the disease.
"After attending the funeral in Bweengwa, they got back to their
homes where they fell ill," she explained.
Nawa said health personnel had since disinfected the affected 70
houses in Ndeema area.
Nawa said her office was making frantic efforts to alert Monze
district commissioner Joyce Nondo on the prevalence of cholera in
Bweengwa area.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Zambia showing the location of the Namwala district is shown at:
<http://www.kaingu-lodge.com/images/ksl-zmbmap.gif>. Although the
western border of Zambia borders on Angola, Namwala in in the central
area. - Mod.LL]
