[4] Cholera - Angola (Luanda, Bengo)
Date: Thu, 13 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=432506>

At least 5 people out of 431 cases died from cholera in the last 24
hours in Luanda province, the provincial health director announced on
Thu, 13 Apr 2006.
According to Vita Vemba, of the 5 deaths, 3 occurred in Cacuaco
district, 2 died while being transferred from Barra do Dande, Bengo
province, to Luanda, one in Maianga district and the other in
Ingombota.
He added that 174 cases were registered in Sambizanga district, and
in Cacuaco 94, most of the patients coming from Bengo province,
Ingombota 43, Cazenga 42, Maianga 28, Viana 20, Samba 15, Kilamba
Kiaxi 14, and one in Rangel.
Since the outbreak of the disease on 13 Feb 2006, there have been 100
deaths out of 4731 cases.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
