[6] Cholera - Angola (Benguela)
Date: Fri, 14 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and Angola Press Agency (Luanda) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200604140057.html>

Last Weds, 13 Apr 2006, the total number of cholera cases was 19,
including 3 deaths, announced by the [health?] department of Cubal
district, 171 kilometres from Benguela city. According to the
source, the spread of this endemic is more pronounced in highly
populous wards such as Camunda, Calomanga and Casseque, the latter
where a lagoon, water storage and treatment center are located.
The latest data for the area indicated 7 cases of cholera without any
loss of life.
